Rate: 20 widgets/hour
Hours per day: 8 hours
Days per week: 5 days
Total widgets per week = Rate × Hours per day × Days per week
Total widgets per week = 20 widgets/hour × 8 hours/day × 5 days/week
Total widgets per week = 20 × 8 × 5
Total widgets per week = 20 ×  addNew hours
Total widgets per week = 20 × 8 × 5 = 20 × 40 = 800
However, we need to consider that the widgets are being assembled. The rate of production is 20 widgets per hour. The number of hours worked per day is 8. The number of days worked per week is 5. So the total number of widgets produced per week is:
Rate × Time per day × Time per week
20 widgets/hour × 8 hours/day × 5 days/week
= 20 × 8 × 5
= 20 × 40
= 800
The problem asks for the total number of widgets John makes in a week. We are given that John can make 20 widgets per hour and works for 8 hours a day. He works 5 days a week.
Total widgets per day = 20 widgets/hour * 8 hours/day = 160 widgets/day
Total widgets per week = 160 widgets/day * 5 days/week = 800 widgets/week
Therefore, John makes 800 widgets per week.

